    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-07-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-07-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="279"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d279">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Webb</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 174.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-07-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 28, 1866</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have to acknowledge the receipt of despatch No.
                    12 of Mr. Lidgerwood, of the 2d of July. It contains an account of certain
                    conversations which took place between himself, joined with acting Rear-Admiral
                    Godon, and the Brazilian minister for foreign affairs, on the subject of the
                    obstruction, by the Allies, of the passage of the United States minister (Mr.
                    Washburn) to Paraguay.</p>
                <p>The conversation which has thus been reported to this department as maintained,
                    on the part of the United States, in those interviews, by Mr. Lidgerwood and the
                    admiral, is approved by the President.</p>
                <p>We wait with serious interest for information of the decision of the Brazilian
                    government upon the subject discussed.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James Watson Webb,</hi> Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic"
                            >c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic"
                        >c</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
